, 
<figureCitation box="[737,783,332,356]" captionStart="FIGURES 221 – 232" captionStartId="110.[151,264,1819,1842]" captionTargetBox="[226,1352,193,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@110.[221,1362,193,1804]" captionTargetPageId="110" captionText="FIGURES 221 – 232. Socii of Argyresthia spp. 221, A. (Argyresthia) decurtata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12334, paratype; 222, A. (A.) minutisocia, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12438, holotype; 223, A. (A.) scalprata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12134, holotype; 224, A. (A.) grammosacca, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12439, paratype; 225, A. (A.) campylotropa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12443, holotype; 226, A. (A.) punctuata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12534, holotype; 227, A. (A.) trochaula Meyrick, slide no. LTT 12335; 228, A. (A.) chlorella, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12337, holotype; 229, A. (A.) subrimosa Meyrick, slide no. LTT 12713; 230, A. (A.) aphoristis Meyrick, slide no. LTT 12348; 231, A. (A.) triangulata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12362, paratype; 232, A. (A.) subzonata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12338, holotype. (Scales = 0.1 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827824/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">221</figureCitation>
): Tuba analis shorter than width of valva. Socius covered with 21̄28 scale-like setae, bearing one or two setae posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[913,1024,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 209 – 220" captionStartId="109.[151,264,1817,1840]" captionTargetBox="[229,1344,195,1793]" captionTargetId="figure@109.[224,1358,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="109" captionText="FIGURES 209 – 220. Socii of Argyresthia spp. 209, A. (Argyresthia) trigonophylla, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12816, paratype; 210, A. (A.) chiotorna, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12757, paratype; 211, A. (A.) hirsuta, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12841, holotype; 212, A. (A.) papillata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12815, holotype; 213, A. (A.) acuminata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12740, holotype; 214, A. (A.) curvativa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12853, holotype; 215, A. (A.) atomata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12804, holotype; 216, A. (A.) orthocera, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12774, holotype; 217, A. (A.) cardiopetala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12432, paratype; 218, A. (A.) mala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12784, paratype; 219, A. (A.) longa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12493, holotype; 220, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12842, holotype. (Scales = 0.1 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827822/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs. 220</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1037,1083,368,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 221 – 232" captionStartId="110.[151,264,1819,1842]" captionTargetBox="[226,1352,193,1803]" captionTargetId="figure@110.[221,1362,193,1804]" captionTargetPageId="110" captionText="FIGURES 221 – 232. Socii of Argyresthia spp. 221, A. (Argyresthia) decurtata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12334, paratype; 222, A. (A.) minutisocia, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12438, holotype; 223, A. (A.) scalprata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12134, holotype; 224, A. (A.) grammosacca, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12439, paratype; 225, A. (A.) campylotropa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12443, holotype; 226, A. (A.) punctuata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12534, holotype; 227, A. (A.) trochaula Meyrick, slide no. LTT 12335; 228, A. (A.) chlorella, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12337, holotype; 229, A. (A.) subrimosa Meyrick, slide no. LTT 12713; 230, A. (A.) aphoristis Meyrick, slide no. LTT 12348; 231, A. (A.) triangulata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12362, paratype; 232, A. (A.) subzonata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12338, holotype. (Scales = 0.1 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827824/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">221</figureCitation>
). Gnathos not inflated distally, without long thick setae apically. Valva widest at middle, dorsal margin arched before middle; a row of thick setae from disc near ventral margin to distal area. Saccus shorter than width of valva, with distal half conspicuously attenuate to narrowly rounded apex. Phallus curved at basal 3/5, 3.5 to 4.0 times as long as width of valva (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 162 – 165" captionStartId="99.[151,264,1942,1965]" captionTargetBox="[217,1365,232,1884]" captionTargetId="figure@99.[181,1405,193,1921]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURES 162 – 165. Phallus of Argyresthia spp. 162, A. (Argyresthia) mala, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12784, paratype; 163, A. (A.) longa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12493, holotype; 164, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12842, holotype; 165, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12334, paratype. (Scales = 0.2 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827804/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs. 164, 165</figureCitation>
). Second sternite with about 13̄15 micro-setae in each row; eighth sternite V-shaped. Coremata present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,151,1797]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,395,548,573]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[410,574,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 268 – 270" captionStartId="118.[151,264,1953,1976]" captionTargetBox="[239,1395,232,1886]" captionTargetId="figure@118.[177,1409,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="118" captionText="FIGURES 268 – 270. Female genitalia of Argyresthia spp. 268, A. (Argyresthia) longa, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12492, paratype; 269, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12791, paratype; 270, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., slide no. LTT 12333, paratype. (Scales = 0.5 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827840/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Figs. 269, 270</figureCitation>
): Ovipositor 2.8 times as long as eighth segment. Anterior apophysis about 7/ 10 length of posterior, bifurcated before middle, branches fused, forming ventral margin of ostium bursae. Lamella postvaginalis narrowly band-shaped. Antrum tubular or slightly funnel-shaped, 1/3 length of eighth segment. Ductus bursae densely spinulate before and near opening of ductus seminalis; ductus seminalis originating from anterior 2/5 of ductus bursae. Corpus bursae oval, with dense micro-spines and denticles; signum with basal plate band-shaped, uniform in width, horns extending outward obliquely or horizontally, broad V-shaped, or nearly straight on anterior margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1437,151,1797]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,799,824]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Variation</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[326,411,799,824]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="77.[151,264,1916,1939]" captionTargetBox="[225,1370,276,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@77.[194,1399,193,1894]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Adults of Argyresthia spp. 36, A. (Argyresthia) cardiopetala, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 37, A. (A.) mala, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 38, A. (A.) longa, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 39, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 40, A. (A.) decurtata, sp. nov., dark form, ♂, paratype; 41, A. (A.) minutisocia, sp. nov., ♀, paratype; 42, A. (A.) scalprata, sp. nov., ♂, holotype; 43, A. (A.) grammosacca, sp. nov., ♀, paratype. (Scales = 2.0 mm)" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/827760/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
): Some specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[684,887,799,824]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Guizhou Province</collectingRegion>
darker; thorax and tegula dark fuscous; forewing grayish fuscous; costa with a row of yellowish-white dots from basal 
<date box="[944,1070,836,861]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" value="2010-05-02" valueMax="2010-07-02" valueMin="2010-05-02">2/5 to 7/10</date>
, with two larger yellow spots at distal 3/10 and before apex; termen with several yellowish-white dots; dorsum with an indistinct V-shaped dark fuscous pattern at basal 1/4 open to costa, reaching near base of costa and middle of cell; dorsal streak dark fuscous, reaching near distal end of cell; tornus with a dark fuscous dot. Some variation in horn shape of signum in female genital.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
